<TITLE> Women's Kabaddi League gets underway Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 8 (bdnews24.com) - Exim Bank Women's Kabaddi League, organised by Bangladesh Kabaddi Federation (BKF), gets underway at Outer Stadium Kabaddi Court Thursday with six clubs participating in the third meet. "We hope the meet would be a competitive one as no team is rated high after 12 national players have been equally distributed among six teams," said BKF general secretary Nazrul Islam at a press conference at the National Sports Council Tuesday. The first-ever women's league was held in 1981 and the second one in 2001. Six clubs, split into two groups, will play the league basis matches and ,later on, top two clubs will qualify for the semifinals scheduled for January 13. The final will take place on January 14. The players for the first time took part in players' transfer and the federation played a key role in the bourse by distributing players equally among the participating clubs to ensure a competitive meet. National players Jahanara and Maleka of Jatrabari KC got the highest amount of Tk 10,000 and Tk 8,000 respectively while others received Tk 4,000 to 3,000 in the transfer, informed Islam. Islam said that they also organised a three-week training camp for participating 35 players, who were picked across the country. Hyder Ali Mia, senior executive vice president of sponsor Exim Bank, said they might continue to sponsor the women's league in future as the board of directors decided to sponsor the league this time. Of the estimated budget of Tk 3.5 lakh, Exim Bank will give Tk 2.5 lakh. Participating clubs: Jatrabari KC, Azad SC, Matuail Milon Smriti Sangsad, Victoria SC, Dhaka Wanderers Club and Jurain Janata Club. 
